### 2.6 Navigation Flow

```
/setup (WizardStep 1)
   ↓ Next (validates Step 1)
/setup (WizardStep 2)
   ↓ Next (validates Step 2)
/setup (WizardStep 3)
   ↓ Next (validates Step 3, at least 1 subject required)
/setup (WizardStep 4)
   ↓ Next (validates Step 4 — overlap check + time range)
/setup (WizardStep 5)
   ↓ Next OR Skip (Step 5 is optional per SRD Section 10.1.e)
/setup (Review screen)
   ↓ Finish → API calls → redirect to /dashboard
```

The wizard is a **single route** (`/setup`). The `currentStep` is an integer in `SetupWizard.jsx` state. No URL-based step navigation — URL changes are only needed when the wizard is done (redirect to `/dashboard`).

**Why no URL-based steps?**

The SRD does not require deep-linking into wizard steps. URL-based steps would add router complexity with zero documented benefit. The simplest implementation wins (AI_DEVELOPMENT_RULES Rule 11, Golden Rule).

**Why redirect to `/dashboard` after finish?**

SRD Section 10.2 says: after Plan Generation, the user "lands on Dashboard." The wizard itself doesn't generate a plan — that's the user's next manual action via the "Generate Plan" button on the Dashboard. So the wizard redirects to `/dashboard`.

