### 2.10 WizardProgressBar

Displays 5 numbered step indicators. The current step is visually highlighted. Completed steps show a checkmark icon. Future steps are grayed out.

**Why 5 steps, not 6 (not counting Review)?**

The SRD defines 5 data entry steps. The Review screen is the submission confirmation, not a data entry step. The progress bar tracks data steps only.

---

### 2.11 Responsive Design

The wizard will be usable on desktop screens (the primary target for an MVP local-first app) but will not break on tablet-sized viewports. No mobile-specific layout is required by the SRD in MVP.

Tailwind classes will use responsive prefixes (`sm:`, `md:`) only where needed to prevent overflow on smaller screens.

